{% from "components/avatar-text/macro.njk" import avatarText %}
{% from "components/avatar/macro.njk" import avatar %}

<h2>Inside an Avatar</h2>
<p>By default <code>AvatarText</code> is
  <code>aria-hidden</code> because its parent
  <a href="/components/avatar/"><code>Avatar</code></a> carries
  the accessible name. The initials are decorative.</p>

<p>
  {% call avatar({ label: "Jane Smith" }) %}
    {{ avatarText({ text: "JS" }) }}
  {% endcall %}
  Jane Smith
</p>

<h2>Standalone with decorative=false</h2>
<p>Set <code>decorative: false</code> to expose the text, and pass
  a <code>label</code> to clarify what the initials mean.</p>

<p>
  {{ avatarText({ text: "JS", decorative: false, label: "Jane Smith's initials" }) }}
</p>
